TRIBUTES have been paid to a rescue dog that helped find bodies in the rubble of Clutha and Stockline, as well as searching for murdered Edinburgh woman Suzanne Pilley. Rescue dog tribute TRIBUTES have been paid to a rescue dog that helped find bodies in the rubble of Clutha and Stockline, as well as searching for murdered Edinburgh woman Suzanne Pilley.Glen the border collie, a servant of the Trossachs Search and Rescue Team for more than 10 years, died yesterday as a result of a suspected stroke.The 15-year-old dog retired from service in May, bowing out at the 10-year memorial of the Stockline Plastics gas explosion.Glen identified a location where one of the victims was trapped. 